name: cytochrome-c oxidase
classes: Acting on a heme group of donors;
reaction: 4 ferrocytochrome c + O2 + 4 H+ = 4 ferricytochrome c + 2 H2O [RN:R00081]
comment: A cytochrome of the a type containing copper. The reduction of O2 to water is accompanied by the extrusion of four protons from the intramitochondrial compartment. Several bacteria appear to contain analogous oxidases.
